  "_comment": "The 6 evolution branches and their 12 final forms. When a creature's affinity for a branch crosses its threshold, it evolves down that branch — the FORM within the branch is rolled: common (usually 85%) or the rare variant (`rareChance`). PASS 3: every evolved form now has an `influence` — an aura that channels branch affinity into OTHER creatures working within `radius` tiles (Chebyshev), stacking with decor. This is the recursive loop: evolve one fire creature and its aura nudges neighbors toward fire too. Rare forms have stronger, wider auras. `color` on the branch is used for affinity bars, auras and particles. Placeholder shapes — swap for art later; keep ids stable. ART PASS: each form's `sprite` maps to public/assets/wildkin/creatures/<sprite>.png (underscored filenames); missing files fall back to placeholder shapes.",
